    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AbstractBinaryTree<E>
    An abstract base class providing some functionality of the BinaryTree interface.
    AbstractHashMap<K,V>
    An abstract base class supporting Map implementations that use hash tables with MAD compression.
    AbstractMap<K,V>
    An abstract base class to ease the implementation of the Map interface.
    AbstractPriorityQueue<K,V>
    An abstract base class to ease the implementation of the PriorityQueue interface.
    AbstractSortedMap<K,V>
    An abstract base class to ease the implementation of the SortedMap interface.
    AbstractTree<E>
    An abstract base class providing some functionality of the Tree interface.
    AdaptablePriorityQueue<K,V>
    Interface for the adaptable priority queue ADT.
    AdjacencyMapGraph<V,E>
    An implementation for a graph structure using an adjacency map for each vertex.
    ArrayList<E>
    Realization of a list by means of a dynamic array.
    ArrayQueue<E>
    Implementation of the queue ADT using a fixed-length array.
    ArrayStack<E>
    Implementation of the stack ADT using a fixed-length array.
    AVLTreeMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a sorted map using an AVL tree.
    BinaryTree<E>
    An interface for a binary tree, in which each node has at most two children.
    ChainHashMap<K,V>
     
    CircularlyLinkedList<E>
    An implementation of a circularly linked list.
    CircularQueue<E>
    This provides one additional method not part of the general Queue interface.
    Colectivo
    Representa un colectivo que recorre una línea con una capacidad limitada de pasajeros y asientos.
    Configuracion
    Clase que representa la configuración inicial del sistema, cargando los parámetros desde un archivo de propiedades.
    DefaultComparator<E>
    Comparator based on the compareTo method of a Comparable element type.
    Deque<E>
    Interface for a double-ended queue: a collection of elements that can be inserted and removed at both ends; this interface is a simplified version of java.util.Deque.
    DoublyLinkedList<E>
    A basic doubly linked list implementation.
    Edge<E>
    An edge of a graph.
    Entry<K,V>
    Interface for a key-value pair.
    GestorSimulacion
    Clase responsable de gestionar la simulación de recorridos de colectivos, controlando la subida y bajada de pasajeros, el cálculo de la ocupación y la satisfacción de los usuarios.
    Graph<V,E>
    An interface for a graph structure.
    GraphAlgorithms
    A collection of graph algorithms.
    GraphExamples
    This class provides a utility to build a graph from a list of edges.
    HeapAdaptablePriorityQueue<K,V>
    An implementation of an adaptable priority queue using an array-based heap.
    HeapPriorityQueue<K,V>
    An implementation of a priority queue using an array-based heap.
    LectorLineas
    Clase utilitaria para leer desde un archivo la definición de las líneas de colectivo y construir objetos Linea con su recorrido de paradas.
    LectorParadas
    Clase utilitaria para cargar las paradas desde un archivo de texto plano.
    Linea
    Representa una línea de colectivo, compuesta por un código identificador y una lista de paradas que conforman su recorrido.
    LinkedBinaryTree<E>
    Concrete implementation of a binary tree using a node-based, linked structure.
    LinkedCircularQueue<E>
    Realization of a circular FIFO queue as an adaptation of a CircularlyLinkedList.
    LinkedPositionalList<E>
    Implementation of a positional list stored as a doubly linked list.
    LinkedQueue<E>
    Realization of a FIFO queue as an adaptation of a SinglyLinkedList.
    LinkedStack<E>
    Realization of a stack as an adaptation of a SinglyLinkedList.
    List<E>
    A simplified version of the java.util.List interface.
    Map<K,V>
    An interface for an associative map which binds a key uniquely to a value.
    Parada
    Representa una parada dentro de una línea de colectivo.
    Partition<E>
    A Union-Find structure for maintaining disjoint sets.
    Pasajero
    Representa un pasajero que desea realizar un viaje en colectivo, indicando su destino, cantidad de intentos, si logró subir y si viajó sentado.
    Position<E>
    An interface for a position which is an abstraction for the location at which a single element is stored in a positional container.
    PositionalList<E>
    An interface for positional lists.
    PriorityQueue<K,V>
    Interface for the priority queue ADT.
    ProbeHashMap<K,V>
     
    Queue<E>
    Interface for a queue: a collection of elements that are inserted and removed according to the first-in first-out principle.
    RBTreeMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a sorted map using a red-black tree.
    Simulador
    Clase principal que ejecuta la simulación de líneas de colectivos.
    SinglyLinkedList<E>
    A basic singly linked list implementation.
    SortedMap<K,V>
    A map with additional support for keys from a total ordering.
    SortedPriorityQueue<K,V>
    An implementation of a priority queue with a sorted list.
    SortedTableMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a map using a sorted table.
    SplayTreeMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a sorted map using a splay tree.
    Stack<E>
    A collection of objects that are inserted and removed according to the last-in first-out principle.
    TestConfiguracion
    Clase de pruebas unitarias para la clase Configuracion.
    TestIndiceSatisfaccion
    Pruebas unitarias para validar el cálculo del índice de satisfacción en GestorSimulacion.
    TestPasajeroReal
    Pruebas unitarias para validar el comportamiento real de los pasajeros en el proceso de subir y bajar del colectivo durante la simulación.
    Tree<E>
    An interface for a tree where nodes can have an arbitrary number of children.
    TreeMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a sorted map using a binary search tree.
    UnsortedPriorityQueue<K,V>
    An implementation of a priority queue with an unsorted list.
    UnsortedTableMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a map using an unsorted table.
    Vertex<V>
    A vertex of a graph.
